From: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
Date: Fri, 03 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] net: ethernet: qualcomm: ppe: offload VLAN-aware bridges

Extend the bridge offload to VLAN-aware bridges. Each VLAN of an
offloaded bridge is backed by its own VSI: ingress VLAN translation
rules assign tagged packets of the member ports and untagged packets
of the PVID ports to the VSI, and the per-VSI egress tag modes provide
tagged or untagged egress per port, with the CPU port always tagged so
the software ports of the bridge see the VLAN of flooded packets. The
per-port default C-VID supplies the VLAN ID when a packet received
untagged on a PVID port leaves through a tagged port.

The translation rules match by ingress port bitmap, so they scale with
the number of VLANs rather than ports times VLANs: all member ports of
a VLAN share one rule, and the ports with a common PVID share another.
Ports of a VLAN-aware bridge drop packets that miss the translation
rules, which implements the ingress side of VLAN filtering. Running
out of the 64 VSIs or the 128 rules fails the VLAN object, falling
back to software for that VLAN only; toggling vlan_filtering on an
offloaded bridge stays refused in both directions.

The VSI state moves from the port to the VSI table: memberships,
untagged and PVID port bitmaps live per VSI now, FDB events carry the
VLAN ID and resolve their VSI through it, and the FDB synchronization
reports learned entries with the VLAN ID of their VSI.

Signed-off-by: Kenneth Kasilag <kenneth@kasilag.me>
---
